        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2020-04-19 11:25:03.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2: Code-Review-1\n\nWe sure cannot remove or change those entries",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "2bab905a4b44bdd0c285a45c70c1bb46fb2b3015",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 5269,
          "name": "Michael Morris",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "michael.morris@est.tech",
          "username": "MichaelMorris"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2020-04-20 15:36:58.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nIf we leave this as is then tosca produced by SDC cannot be parsed by a tosca parser unless it is forgiving of such type-value errors. Is the concern that changing from boolean to string will break other applications? Do you know which applications use these two metadata values?",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "1429db5cbe445e35375e9a12a75aedd29095c9e0",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 653,
          "name": "Ofir Sonsino",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "ofirson@gmail.com",
          "username": "os0695"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2020-04-21 14:30:27.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nVID and SO at the least, possibly more.\nIf they commit to align to this change we can proceed, as long as a migration task will be delivered too for existing environments",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "a87a3b15f2a857b91decea41a7757bafc6c4b1c4",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 5269,
          "name": "Michael Morris",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "michael.morris@est.tech",
          "username": "MichaelMorris"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2020-04-23 09:28:21.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> Patch Set 2:\n> \n> VID and SO at the least, possibly more.\n> If they commit to align to this change we can proceed, as long as a migration task will be delivered too for existing environments\n\nHi Ofir,\nI was looking at the SDC tosca parser code and it looks like it converts the metadata values to String before returning to any application reading it so there would be no impact, see getValue() and getAllProperties() methods here, both return the metadata propoerty value as a String:\nhttps://gerrit.onap.org/r/gitweb?p=sdc/sdc-tosca.git;a=blob;f=jtosca/src/main/java/org/onap/sdc/toscaparser/api/elements/Metadata.java;h=f3de49ea95ed58424160119e93c31d0c752491db;hb=ff780791b9c8b2af2aaf5d14d250b8612928b273\nIf Im reading this correct then there would no impact on applications in which case it could be safe to proceed with this change. Let me know your thoughts. Thanks",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "5f8ec5a94fd0ffa736b7003d82bc9b9e86348569",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 653,
